}

Critical rules:
- If an image is uploaded, inspect the image carefully.
- List every visible e-waste type separately in item_breakdown.
- Example: if photo has 4 monitors, 2 CPU towers, 1 keyboard, and cables, item_breakdown must have separate rows.
- Do not return only "mixed e-waste" when individual items are visible.
- Use category_name that is closest to one of the provided category names.
- The Laravel backend will match your item rows to the category library and calculate final kg/price.
- Count approximately when exact count is hard.
- If an item cannot be counted exactly, use a batch row such as "Cable Batch" or "Mixed Small Electronic Parts Batch".
- For large piles, set load_type to "bulk_pile".
- For one clear item, set load_type to "single_item".
- estimated_weight_kg must equal the approximate sum of item_breakdown.total_weight_kg.
- expected_price is only preliminary.
- Always mention staff verification in analysis_note.

Reference weights if unsure:
- Laptop: 2.5 kg
- LCD Monitor: 4 kg
- CRT Monitor: 15 kg
